<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 23. Odostomia (s. l.) sp. 1, Haifa Bay, Israel, NM project (sample HM 27 (c )): front (A, B), side (C, D) and back (E, F) views, detail of the adapical part of the body whorl showing the extremely faint spiral microsculpture (G), virtual section through the apical spire showing the columella of the intorted protoconch (H) and apical view of the protoconch (I; surface partly corroded). The pink hue is due to staining with eosin solution. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-F); 0.2 mm (G-I)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/496976" .

